      "content": "```python\ndef smooth_gps(measurements, process_variance, measurement_variance):\n    # Kalman filter implementation with process and measurement variance\n    estimated_measurements = [measurements[0]]\n    P = process_variance  # Initial error covariance\n    for i in range(1, len(measurements)):\n        # Prediction step\n        predicted_measurement = estimated_measurements[-1]\n        P = P + process_variance  # Update error covariance\n        \n        # Update step\n        kalman_gain = P / (P + measurement_variance)\n        estimated_measurement = predicted_measurement + kalman_gain * (measurements[i] - predicted_measurement)\n        P = (1 - kalman_gain) * P  # Update error covariance\n        \n        estimated_measurements.append(estimated_measurement)\n    return estimated_measurements\n```\nThis should now correctly handle the error covariance updates and match the expected output for your test.",
